<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-06-01T06:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-06-01T06:00:00-05:00" n="85" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d85">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 Pacific War/3929: Telegram</note>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Gauss</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                        </hi>
                    </head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Chungking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-06-01T18:00:00+07:00">June 1, 1944—6
                                p.m.</date>
                            <lb/> [Received June 1—2:45 p.m.]</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>956. Director [of] Foreign Office’s European Department<note n="87" xml:id="d85fn87">Lone Liang.</note> last evening said privately to
                        Counselor that he did not believe “rumors” that Japan and Soviet Russia had
                        come to agreement and did not believe more than two divisions Jap troops had
                        been moved from Manchuria into China proper. He said Japs could move some
                        troops out of Manchuria without much risk because Soviets had probably
                        transferred some Siberian forces to European theatre. He considered present
                        military situation Honan and Yangtze Valley serious, with possibility
                        Changsha would be lost before long.</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Gauss</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>